<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Scotsman service</p>
    <h2>Scotsman: Ali Group, Vernon Hills, EnergyStar focus, Brilliance pioneered nugget ice.</h2>

    <p>Scotsman Industries is a major US commercial ice machine manufacturer, part of Ali Group (Italian privately-held foodservice holding company with approximately 25 brands including Scotsman, sister Ice-O-Matic, Beverage-Air refrigeration, Champion dishwashers, Carpigiani gelato). Scotsman US HQ Vernon Hills, Illinois. Manufacturing since 1950.</p>

    <p>Two flagship lines define Scotsman:</p>

    <p><strong>Prodigy ELITE cube ice</strong> is Scotsman's signature cube line. C0322 (300 lb/day modular), C0530 (500 lb/day), C0630 (600 lb/day), C0830 (800 lb/day), C1030 (1,000 lb/day), C1448 (1,400 lb/day large modular). Distinctive <strong>horizontal evaporator with spray pump architecture</strong>: water sprayed up onto evaporator from below. More water-efficient than vertical-evap competitors (Manitowoc), but the spray pump adds a service item that vertical-evap machines don't have.</p>

    <p><strong>Brilliance nugget ice</strong>: Scotsman pioneered the commercial nugget ice category. The original "Sonic ice" architecture, now copied by Hoshizaki Sliver Nugget and Manitowoc R-Series, but Scotsman remains the category leader. N0422 (420 lb/day), N0622 (620 lb/day), N0922 (920 lb/day).</p>

    <p>Our techs service the entire Scotsman lineup across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. Plus MV vertical cube (legacy/specialty), SCN small undercounter, EH flake (less common but available), HID dispensers.</p>

    <p>EPA 608 Universal plus R-290 certified (post-2020 Scotsman R-290 transition). BHGS #A49573. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7. Parent context: <a href="/commercial/ice-machines/">commercial ice machine repair</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 LINEUP & WHAT FAILS -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Lineup and architecture</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Scotsman series and what fails on each.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Scotsman's horizontal evaporator with spray pump architecture is fundamentally different from Manitowoc vertical evaporator drip and Hoshizaki cell-and-curtain. The differential matters for diagnosis, not just trivia.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Prodigy ELITE C-Series Cube Ice (Flagship)</h3>
    <p>C0322 (300 lb/day, 22 inch modular), C0530 / C0530MA-1 (500 lb/day, 30 inch), C0630 (600 lb/day, 30 inch), C0830 (800 lb/day, 30 inch), C1030 (1,000 lb/day, 30 inch), C1448 (1,400 lb/day, 48 inch). Air-cooled (-A), water-cooled (W), remote-condensed (R). Common in bars, restaurants, hotels.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Spray Pump Architecture: Critical Service Knowledge</h3>
    <p>Water is held in a sump below the evaporator, sprayed UP onto the evaporator surface by an electric spray pump. <strong>This means Prodigy ELITE has a spray pump that vertical-evap machines don't have.</strong> Spray pump wear at year 6 to 9 is a Scotsman-specific service item. Symptom: spray pattern uneven, ice formation uneven, production drops. Replacement $380 to $540.</p>
    <p>Other common Prodigy ELITE failures:</p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li>Spray pump wear (year 6 to 9), Scotsman-specific, most common Prodigy service item</li>
      <li>Scale buildup on horizontal evaporator, same root cause across architectures, cleaning resolves</li>
      <li>Water inlet valve diaphragm, year 5 to 8 typical</li>
      <li>Hot gas valve / harvest cycle issues, ice frozen to evaporator, won't release</li>
      <li>AutoAlert diagnostic system board, modern Prodigy units</li>
      <li>Compressor capacitor plus start relay (year 8 to 12)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Brilliance Nugget Ice (Original Sonic Ice Pioneer)</h3>
    <p>N0422, N0622, N0922 sizes. Architecture similar to auger-driven flake but with extrusion mechanism compressing ice into nugget shape. Common Brilliance failures: auger gear reducer (year 6 to 9), extrusion mechanism wear (year 7 to 10, Brilliance-specific), auger motor (year 8 to 12), drive shaft seal (year 5 to 7, bar environments faster wear), CO2 sensor on CO2-injected applications.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">MV Vertical Cube Ice (Legacy)</h3>
    <p>MV-Series, older vertical cube architecture, less common. Still serviceable, parts available.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">SCN Compact Undercounter</h3>
    <p>Small undercounter cube. Bars and cafés. Compact form factor with similar Prodigy architecture.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">EH Flake Ice</h3>
    <p>Scotsman's flake offering. Less common in LA than Hoshizaki F-Series, but available. Auger-driven architecture.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">HID Dispenser Series</h3>
    <p>Hotel and hospitality dispensers. Often paired with Prodigy ELITE production.</p>
  </div>
</section>

